1 Okla homa by adding a new Section 44 to Article X thereof, to read as
2 follows:
3 A. There is hereby created a trust fund to be known as the
4 "Oklahoma Veterans Lottery Trust Fund". The trust fund shall
5 consist of funds transferred to it from the Oklahoma Veterans
6 Lottery game.
7 B. Monies in the Oklahoma Veterans Lottery Trust Fund shall
8 only be expended for the following purposes:
9 1. Grants to congressionally-chartered veterans service
10 organizations within the state for operational funding related to
11 youth education programs, assisting veterans in need, and providing
12 service officer funding;
13 2. Grants to individual veterans registered with the Oklahoma
14 Veterans Registry, widows or widowers of veterans, or family members
15 designated as a caretaker by the Department of Veterans Affairs for
16 use during catastrophic emergencies;
17 3. Grants for funding indigent veteran funerals when all other
18 means of funding have been attempted or exhausted; and
19 4. Grants for veteran outreach programs where veteran
20 attendance is greater than fifty percent (50%) of the total
21 attendance to supplement funding needed for operational costs
22 directly related to the programs.
23 C. Funds deposited in the Oklahoma Veterans Lottery Trust Fund
24 shall be administered by the Oklahoma Veterans Trust Fund Board of
Req. No. 11694 Page 2

1 Gove rnors. The Board of Governors shall consist of nine (9)
2 members, one (1) member from each of the following veteran service
3 organizations: Disabled American Veterans, American Legion,
4 Veterans of Foreign Wars, Paralyzed Veterans of America, Vietnam
5 Veterans of America, Military Order of the Purple Heart, the
6 Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs, and two additional members
7 appointed by the Oklahoma Veterans Council. Chartered organizations
8 in good standing with the Secretary of State of Oklahoma shall
9 appoint their members and an alternate to the Board of Governors for
10 a term of two (2) years. No member shall serve more than three
11 terms.
12 D. The Legislature shall appropriate funds from the Oklahoma
13 Veterans Lottery Trust Fund only for the purposes specified in
14 subsection B of this section. The Legislature shall not use funds
15 from the Oklahoma Veterans Lottery Trust Fund to supplant or replace
16 other state funds supporting the military, veterans, or their
17 families.
18 E. In order to ensure that the funds from the trust fund are
19 used to enhance and not supplant funding for the military, veterans
20 or their families, the State Board of Equalization shall examine and
21 investigate appropriations from the Oklahoma Veterans Lottery Trust
22 Fund each year. At the meeting of the State Board of Equalization
23 held within five (5) days after the monthly apportionment in
24 February of each year, the State Board of Equalization shall issue a
Req. No. 11694 Page 3

1 find ing and report, which shall state whether appropriations from
2 the trust fund were used to enhance or supplant military, veteran,
3 or their families' funding. If the State Board of Equalization
4 finds that funding for military, veterans, or their families was
5 supplanted by the funds from the Oklahoma Veterans Lottery Trust
6 Fund, the State Board of Equalization shall specify the amount of
7 funding that was supplanted. If funding is found to have been
8 supplanted, the Legislature shall not make any appropriations for
9 the ensuing fiscal year until an appropriation in the supplanted
10 fund amount is made to replenish the Oklahoma Veterans Lottery Trust
11 Fund.
